article.headline: South Alabama 81, New Orleans 71
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Mario Jointer scored 22 points and three others reached double figures, leading South Alabama to a 81-71 victory over New Orleans on Monday night. Jointer hit 7-of-13 from the field, 5-of-8 free throws and 3-of-6 from behind the arc for the Jaguars (17-6, 8-3 Sun Belt Conference). Jeffrey Collins added 14 points while Richard Law and Leandro Buboltz each scored 13. The teams were tied 36-36 at halftime, but the Jaguars managed to outscore the UNO 45-35 in the second half. Jeremie Davis led UNO (7-16, 4-8) with a game-high 23 points. Nathaniel Parker had 13 and Ernest Daney 11.
